                            <comment id="16072276" author="blerer" created="Mon, 3 Jul 2017 11:21:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When collections are validated the collection elements are validated using the &lt;tt&gt;Serializer::validate&lt;/tt&gt; method. As Tuples and UDFs use a &lt;tt&gt;BytesSerializer&lt;/tt&gt; the validate method does not check if the bytes are valid for the expected Tuple or UDT.&lt;br/&gt;
The patches add some specific serializers for &lt;tt&gt;Tuples&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;UDTs&lt;/tt&gt; that override the &lt;tt&gt;Serializer::validate&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/cassandra-2.2...blerer:13646-2.2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/cassandra-3.0...blerer:13646-3.0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/cassandra-3.11...blerer:13646-3.11&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.11&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/cassandra-trunk...blerer:trunk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;trunk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran the patches on our internal CI and the failing tests seems unrelated to the patches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
